{"id":"perfumes","term":"Perfumes","source":"Easton's Bible Dictionary (M.G. Easton, 1897)","html":"<p>Were used in religious worship, and for personal and domestic enjoyment (<a class=\"ref\" data-ref=\"Exodus 30:35\">Ex. 30:35-37</a>; <a class=\"ref\" data-ref=\"Proverbs 7:17\">Prov. 7:17</a>; <a class=\"ref\" data-ref=\"Song of Solomon 3:6\">Cant. 3:6</a>; <a class=\"ref\" data-ref=\"Isaiah 57:9\">Isa. 57:9</a>); and also in embalming the dead, and in other funeral ceremonies (<a class=\"ref\" data-ref=\"Mark 14:8\">Mark 14:8</a>; <a class=\"ref\" data-ref=\"Luke 24:1\">Luke 24:1</a>; <a class=\"ref\" data-ref=\"John 19:39\">John 19:39</a>).</p>\n\u0000","refs":["Exodus 30:35","Proverbs 7:17","Song of Solomon 3:6","Isaiah 57:9","Mark 14:8","Luke 24:1","John 19:39"]}